gton, D.C. Stafford discusses practical uses of wood past and present, tree diseases and environmental threats, and trees’ potential contributions toward slowing global climate change. Brimming with unusual topics and intriguing facts, this book celebrates trees and their long, long lives as our inspiring and beloved natural companions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aTreeszGreat Britain. 7aNATURE / Plants / Trees.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030020733040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022219740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300222197423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300222197/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY